2
00:00:06,401 --> 00:00:08,426
- How doyou do?
- Pleasure.

3
00:00:08,503 --> 00:00:11,597
Hello,Jack.
Areyou ofthe Boston Dawsons?

4
00:00:11,673 --> 00:00:15,234
No-- the Chippewa Falls Dawsons,
actually.

5
00:00:15,310 --> 00:00:17,005
Oh,yes. Yes.

6
00:00:18,947 --> 00:00:23,441
Hemusthave been nervous,
butheneverfaltered.

7
00:00:23,518 --> 00:00:25,816
Theyassumed
he wasone ofthem--

8
00:00:25,887 --> 00:00:29,482
Heir to a railroadfortune,
perhaps.

9
00:00:29,558 --> 00:00:34,552
Newmoney, obviously,
butstilla memberofthe club.

10
00:00:34,629 --> 00:00:37,928
Mother, ofcourse,
couldalways be countedupon.

11
00:00:37,999 --> 00:00:41,025
Tell us ofthe accommodations
in steerage, Mr. Dawson.

12
00:00:41,103 --> 00:00:43,469
I hearthey're quite good
on this ship.

13
00:00:43,538 --> 00:00:48,100
The best I've seen, ma'am.
Hardly any rats.

14
00:00:48,176 --> 00:00:50,906
( Laughter)

15
00:00:50,979 --> 00:00:53,880
Mr. Dawson isjoining us
from the third class.

16
00:00:53,949 --> 00:00:57,112
He was ofsome assistance
to myfiancee last night.

17
00:00:57,185 --> 00:00:59,915
It turns out that Mr. Dawson
is quite a fine artist.

18
00:00:59,988 --> 00:01:02,752
He was kind enough to show me
some of his worktoday.

19
00:01:02,824 --> 00:01:05,918
Rose and I differ somewhat
in our definition offine art.

20
00:01:05,994 --> 00:01:07,962
Not to impugn yourwork, sir.

21
00:01:09,731 --> 00:01:12,359
( Clears Throat)

22
00:01:13,668 --> 00:01:15,602
Ismay:
She may be mine on paper

23
00:01:15,670 --> 00:01:18,434
but in the eyes ofGod,
she belongs to Thomas Andrews.

24
00:01:18,507 --> 00:01:20,441
( Whispering):
Are these all for me?

25
00:01:20,509 --> 00:01:22,704
Just start from the outside
and workyourway in.

26
00:01:22,778 --> 00:01:25,008
He knows every rivet
in her, don'tyou, Thomas?

27
00:01:25,080 --> 00:01:28,481
- Your ship is a wonder, truly.
- Thankyou, Rose.

28
00:01:31,353 --> 00:01:34,720
- And how doyou takeyour caviar, sir?
- No caviarfor me, thanks.

29
00:01:34,790 --> 00:01:36,724
Never did like it much.

30
00:01:37,993 --> 00:01:41,224
And where, exactly,
doyou live, Mr. Dawson?

31
00:01:41,296 --> 00:01:44,459
Well, right now, my address
is the R.M.S. Titanic.

32
00:01:44,533 --> 00:01:46,933
Afterthat,
I'm on God's good humor.

33
00:01:47,002 --> 00:01:49,334
And how is it
you have means to travel?

34
00:01:49,404 --> 00:01:51,565
I work myway
from place to place--

35
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:53,870
You know,
tramp steamers and such.

36
00:01:53,942 --> 00:01:56,240
But I won myticket
on Titanic here

37
00:01:56,311 --> 00:01:58,472
at a lucky hand at poker.

38
00:01:58,547 --> 00:02:01,607
A very lucky hand.

39
00:02:01,683 --> 00:02:04,083
- All life is a game of luck.
- Mmm.

40
00:02:04,152 --> 00:02:06,086
A real man makes
his own luck, Archie.

41
00:02:06,154 --> 00:02:08,645
- Right, Dawson?
- Mmm.

42
00:02:08,723 --> 00:02:13,524
And you find that sort of
rootless existence appealing, doyou?

43
00:02:15,330 --> 00:02:17,355
Well,yes, ma'am, I do.

44
00:02:17,432 --> 00:02:21,163
I mean, got everything I need
right here with me.

45
00:02:21,236 --> 00:02:24,171
Got air in my lungs
and a few blank sheets of paper.

46
00:02:24,239 --> 00:02:28,107
I mean, I love waking up in the morning
not knowing what's going to happen

47
00:02:28,176 --> 00:02:32,340
orwho I'm going to meet,
where I'm going to wind up.

48
00:02:32,414 --> 00:02:36,145
Just the other night, I was sleeping
under a bridge, and now here I am

49
00:02:36,218 --> 00:02:39,381
on the grandest ship in the world
having champagne with you fine people.

50
00:02:39,454 --> 00:02:42,048
- ( Laughter)
- I'll take some more ofthat.

51
00:02:42,123 --> 00:02:45,251
I figure life's a gift,
and I don't intend on wasting it.

52
00:02:45,327 --> 00:02:49,559
You never know what hand
you're going to get dealt next.

53
00:02:49,631 --> 00:02:53,397
You learn to take life
as it comes atyou. Hereyou go, Cal.

54
00:02:53,468 --> 00:02:56,232
To make each day count.

55
00:02:56,304 --> 00:02:59,398
- Well said,Jack.
- Hear, hear!

56
00:02:59,474 --> 00:03:01,942
To making it count.

57
00:03:03,545 --> 00:03:06,639
- All: To making it count.
- Archie: Bravo.

58
00:03:10,318 --> 00:03:13,583
( MollyLaughing)

59
00:03:13,655 --> 00:03:16,283
Mr. Brown had no idea
I'd hidden the money in the stove.

60
00:03:16,358 --> 00:03:18,292
( Laughter)

61
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:22,820
So he comes home drunk as a pig,
celebrating and he lights a fire.

62
00:03:22,898 --> 00:03:25,662
( Laughter)

63
00:03:25,734 --> 00:03:28,532
( Softly): Next it'll be
brandies in the smoking room.

64
00:03:28,603 --> 00:03:32,733
Archie:
Well,join me in a brandy, gentlemen?

65
00:03:32,807 --> 00:03:34,672
( MenAgree)

66
00:03:34,743 --> 00:03:37,007
Now they retreat into a cloud ofsmoke
and congratulate each other

67
00:03:37,078 --> 00:03:39,103
on being masters ofthe universe.

68
00:03:39,180 --> 00:03:41,307
Ladies, thankyou for
the pleasure ofyour company.

69
00:03:41,383 --> 00:03:44,250
Rose, may I escortyou
backto the cabin?

70
00:03:44,319 --> 00:03:47,982
- No, I'll stay here.
- Hereyou go, Molly.

71
00:03:48,056 --> 00:03:50,388
Archie:
Joining us, Dawson?

72
00:03:50,458 --> 00:03:52,858
You don't want to stay out here
with the women, doyou?

73
00:03:52,928 --> 00:03:54,725
No, thanks.
I've got to be heading back.

74
00:03:54,796 --> 00:03:56,730
- Ah.
- Probably best.

75
00:03:56,798 --> 00:03:59,392
It'll be all business
and politics, that sort ofthing--

76
00:03:59,467 --> 00:04:01,731
Wouldn't interestyou.

77
00:04:01,803 --> 00:04:04,431
But Dawson, good ofyou to come.

78
00:04:09,411 --> 00:04:11,345
Jack, mustyou go?

79
00:04:11,413 --> 00:04:13,938
Time for me to go row
with the other slaves.

80
00:04:17,285 --> 00:04:19,685
Good night, Rose.

81
00:04:46,081 --> 00:04:48,641
( Clock BeginsChiming)

82
