...jurisdiction ofthe Sherman Act
so my lawyers will argue.

111
00:08:02,043 --> 00:08:05,843
That's what Rockefeller said, but
the Supreme Court is not swallowing it.

112
00:08:05,914 --> 00:08:10,351
( MenShoutingAndCheering,
DrumsAndPipes Playing)

113
00:08:25,934 --> 00:08:29,529
What? You think
a first-class girl can't drink?

114
00:08:31,005 --> 00:08:32,996
- ( Squeals)
- Get out of here.

115
00:08:33,074 --> 00:08:35,201
- You all right?
- ( Laughing)

116
00:08:35,276 --> 00:08:38,541
- I'm fine.
- ( Growls)

117
00:08:38,613 --> 00:08:41,207
Two out ofthree,
two out ofthree.

118
00:08:41,282 --> 00:08:43,580
So...

119
00:08:43,651 --> 00:08:46,484
you thinkyou're
big, tough men?

120
00:08:46,554 --> 00:08:48,522
Let's seeyou do this.

121
00:08:49,991 --> 00:08:53,358
Hold this for me,Jack.
Hold it up.

122
00:09:08,176 --> 00:09:10,167
Ow!
( Laughing)

123
00:09:10,245 --> 00:09:13,772
-Jesus, Mary andJoseph!
- You all right?

124
00:09:13,848 --> 00:09:16,544
I haven't done that in years.

125
00:09:23,558 --> 00:09:26,322
Go see Maggie, lads.
Give herthe holley! Let's go!

126
00:09:26,394 --> 00:09:29,295
Musicians:
Ho!

127
00:09:52,220 --> 00:09:54,586
Coffee, sir?

128
00:10:02,697 --> 00:10:05,291
I had hoped you would
come to me last night.

129
00:10:07,302 --> 00:10:10,066
I was tired.

130
00:10:11,439 --> 00:10:14,272
Your exertions below decks
were no doubt exhausting.

131
00:10:16,744 --> 00:10:21,010
I seeyou had that undertaker
ofa manservant follow me. How typical.

132
00:10:21,082 --> 00:10:24,142
You will never behave like that
again, Rose. Doyou understand?

133
00:10:27,522 --> 00:10:31,185
I'm not a foreman in one
ofyour mills thatyou can command.

134
00:10:31,259 --> 00:10:33,921
I'm yourfiancee.

135
00:10:35,563 --> 00:10:37,656
Myfiancee?
Myfiancee?!!

136
00:10:37,732 --> 00:10:39,996
Yes,you are, and mywife!

137
00:10:41,169 --> 00:10:45,902
Mywife in practice if notyet by law,
soyou will honor me.

138
00:10:45,973 --> 00:10:49,204
You will honor me the way a wife
is required to honor a husband.

139
00:10:49,277 --> 00:10:51,370
Because I will not be
made out a fool, Rose.

140
00:10:51,446 --> 00:10:55,007
Is this in anyway unclear?

141
00:10:55,083 --> 00:10:57,711
- No.
- Good.

142
00:10:57,785 --> 00:10:59,719
Excuse me.

143
00:11:04,158 --> 00:11:06,524
Miss Rose!

144
00:11:07,662 --> 00:11:10,096
- We had a little... accident.
- That's all right, Miss Rose.

145
00:11:10,164 --> 00:11:12,132
- That's all right.
- I'm sorry, Trudy.

146
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:15,465
Let me helpyou.
It's all right, miss.

147
00:11:21,142 --> 00:11:23,076
It's all right, miss.

148
00:11:28,249 --> 00:11:31,514
- Tea, Trudy.
- Yes, ma'am.

149
00:11:47,435 --> 00:11:51,872
You're not to see that boy again,
doyou understand me?

150
00:11:51,939 --> 00:11:56,205
- Rose, I forbid it.
- Oh, stop it, Mother.

151
00:11:56,277 --> 00:11:58,541
You'll giveyourself
a nosebleed.

152
00:11:58,613 --> 00:12:00,547
This is not a game.

153
00:12:00,615 --> 00:12:04,517
Our situation is precarious.
You know the money's gone.

154
00:12:04,585 --> 00:12:07,145
Ofcourse I know it's gone.

155
00:12:07,221 --> 00:12:09,314
You remind me every day.

156
00:12:09,390 --> 00:12:15,090
Yourfather left us nothing but a legacy
of bad debts hidden by a good name.

157
00:12:15,163 --> 00:12:18,064
That name is the only card
we have to play.

158
00:12:18,132 --> 00:12:22,466
I don't understand you.
It is a fine match with Hockley.

159
00:12:22,537 --> 00:12:27,998
- It will ensure our survival.
- How can you put this on my shoulders?

160
00:12:28,075 --> 00:12:32,375
- Why areyou being so selfish?
- I'm being selfish?

161
00:12:35,616 --> 00:12:38,881
Doyou want to see me
working as a seamstress?

162
00:12:40,354 --> 00:12:42,982
Is that whatyou want?

163
00:12:44,926 --> 00:12:48,987
To see ourfine things
sold at auction?

164
00:12:49,063 --> 00:12:51,327
Our memories
scattered to the winds?

165
00:13:01,409 --> 00:13:04,071
( Sighs)
It's so unfair.

166
00:13:05,313 --> 00:13:08,441
Ofcourse it's unfair.

167
00:13:08,516 --> 00:13:10,450
We're women.

168
00:13:12,153 --> 00:13:14,781
Our choices are never easy.

169
00:13:21,729 --> 00:13:23,663
Hmm?

170
00:13:35,810 --> 00:13:40,179
Congregation:
" Protect them byThy guardian hand "

171
00:13:40,248 --> 00:13:46,847
" From every peril
on the land. "

172
00:13:46,921 --> 00:13:51,324
" O spirit,
whom the Father sent "

173
00:13:51,392 --> 00:13:56,227
"To spread across
the firmament "

174
00:13:56,297 --> 00:14:00,825
" O wind of heaven,
byThy might "

175
00:14:00,902 --> 00:14:06,033
" Save all who dare
the eagle's flight "

176
00:14:06,107 --> 00:14:10,305
"And keep them
byThywatchful... "

177
00:14:12,680 --> 00:14:15,080
- Hello, Mr. Andrews.
- Hello,Jack.

178
00:14:23,991 --> 00:14:27,154
- Sir.
- I need to talkto somebodyfor a sec.

179
00:14:27,228 --> 00:14:29,719
You're not supposed
to be in here.

180
00:14:29,797 --> 00:14:33,324
" ...fire and foe
Protect them... "

181
00:14:33,401 --> 00:14:35,301
I wasjust here last night.
You don't remember me?

182
00:14:35,369 --> 00:14:37,894
No, I'm afraid I don't.
Nowyou're going to have to turn around.

183
00:14:37,972 --> 00:14:40,372
He'll tell you.
I just-- I just need--

184
00:14:40,441 --> 00:14:43,808
Mr. Hockley
and Mrs. Dewitt Bukater

185
00:14:43,878 --> 00:14:46,813
continue to be appreciative
ofyour assistance.

186
00:14:46,881 --> 00:14:50,578
They asked me to, uh...
giveyou this in gratitude.

187
00:14:50,651 --> 00:14:53,711
- I don't wantyour money. Please, l--
- And also to remind you...

188
00:14:53,788 --> 00:14:55,847
thatyou hold
a third-class ticket

189
00:14:55,923 --> 00:14:58,448
and thatyour presence here
is no longer appropriate.

190
00:14:58,526 --> 00:15:00,460
Please, I just want
to speakto Rose for--

191
00:15:00,528 --> 00:15:04,464
Gentlemen, will you please see that
Mr. Dawson gets to where he belongs

192
00:15:04,532 --> 00:15:06,727
and that he stays there?

193
00:15:06,801 --> 00:15:09,736
Yes, sir.
Come along,you.

194
00:15:11,539 --> 00:15:14,702
" Oh, hear us
when we cryto Thee "

195
00:15:14,775 --> 00:15:20,577
" Forthose in peril
on the sea. "

196
00:15:20,648 --> 00:15:22,673
Ruth: And why doyou have
two steering wheels?

197
00:15:22,750 --> 00:15:24,684
We really only use
this near shore.

198
00:15:24,752 --> 00:15:27,983
Excuse me, sir. Another ice warning.
This one's from the Noordam.

199
00:15:28,055 --> 00:15:30,649
Thankyou, Sparks.

200
00:15:31,993 --> 00:15:35,485
Oh, not to worry.
Quite normal forthis time ofyear.

201
00:15:35,563 --> 00:15:37,622
In fact, we're speeding up.

202
00:15:37,698 --> 00:15:40,462
I'vejust ordered
the last boilers lit.

203
00:15:44,238 --> 00:15:47,298
Man: Okay, son,
wind it up tight like I showed you.

204
00:15:47,375 --> 00:15:49,809
Okay, now, let it go.

205
00:15:52,113 --> 00:15:54,638
- Was good, wasn't it?
- Quite nice.

206
00:15:54,715 --> 00:15:57,240
That's excellent, son.

207
00:16:01,222 --> 00:16:04,658
Rose:
Mr. Andrews, forgive me...

208
00:16:04,725 --> 00:16:08,092
I did the sum in my head
and with the number of lifeboats

209
00:16:08,162 --> 00:16:10,596
times the capacityyou mentioned

210
00:16:10,665 --> 00:16:14,260
forgive me, but it seems that there
are not enough for everyone aboard.

211
00:16:14,335 --> 00:16:17,361
About half, actually.

212
00:16:17,438 --> 00:16:22,034
Rose,you miss nothing, doyou?
ln fact, I put in these new type davits

213
00:16:22,109 --> 00:16:24,976
which can take an extra row
of boats inside this one

214
00:16:25,046 --> 00:16:29,380
but it was thought by some
that the deckwould looktoo cluttered

215
00:16:29,450 --> 00:16:32,510
so I was overruled.

216
00:16:32,586 --> 00:16:35,749
Waste ofdeck space as it is
on an unsinkable ship.

217
00:16:35,823 --> 00:16:40,453
Sleep soundly,young Rose. I have built
you a good ship, strong and true.

218
00:16:40,528 --> 00:16:42,462
She's all the lifeboatyou need.

219
00:16:42,530 --> 00:16:46,022
Just keep heading aft.
The next stop will be the engine room.

220
00:16:46,100 --> 00:16:48,295
Come on.

221
00:16:50,771 --> 00:16:55,367
Jack, this is impossible.
I can't seeyou.

222
00:16:55,443 --> 00:16:59,903
- I need to talktoyou.
- No,Jack, no.

223
00:16:59,980 --> 00:17:03,040
Jack, I'm engaged.

224
00:17:03,117 --> 00:17:07,178
I'm marrying Cal.
I love Cal.

225
00:17:09,457 --> 00:17:13,257
Rose,you're no picnic.

226
00:17:13,327 --> 00:17:16,125
All right,you're a spoiled
little brat, even

227
00:17:16,197 --> 00:17:20,998
but underthatyou're the most
amazingly astounding

228
00:17:21,068 --> 00:17:25,198
wonderful girl-- woman--
that I've ever known and...

229
00:17:25,272 --> 00:17:27,763
-Jack, l...
- No, let me try and get this out.

230
00:17:27,842 --> 00:17:31,573
You're,you're ama--

231
00:17:31,645 --> 00:17:34,978
I'm not an idiot.
I know how the world works.

232
00:17:35,049 --> 00:17:36,983
I've got ten bucks
in my pocket.

233
00:17:37,051 --> 00:17:39,849
I have nothing to offeryou
and I know that.

234
00:17:39,920 --> 00:17:42,616
I understand.

235
00:17:42,690 --> 00:17:46,820
