I thinkthey're very good, sir.

485
00:44:16,749 --> 00:44:19,809
Don't touch anything.
I want the entire room photographed.

486
00:44:19,885 --> 00:44:22,285
Rose:
Just keep holding my hand.

487
00:44:24,457 --> 00:44:26,891
We've been looking
foryou, miss.

488
00:44:30,096 --> 00:44:32,894
Rose ( Sighs):
Well, here we go.

489
00:44:38,938 --> 00:44:41,668
Something serious has happened.

490
00:44:41,741 --> 00:44:43,675
Yes, it has.

491
00:44:44,777 --> 00:44:48,235
Indeed. Two things dearto me
have disappeared this evening.

492
00:44:48,314 --> 00:44:51,681
Now that one is back I have a pretty
good idea where to find the other.

493
00:44:51,751 --> 00:44:54,276
- Search him.
- Takeyour coat off, sir.

494
00:44:54,353 --> 00:44:56,287
- Now what?
- Come on.

495
00:44:56,355 --> 00:45:00,121
Cal, what areyou doing? We're in the
middle ofan emergency. What's going on?

496
00:45:00,192 --> 00:45:02,319
- Is this it?
- That's it.

497
00:45:02,395 --> 00:45:04,693
This is horseshit!

498
00:45:04,764 --> 00:45:08,427
- Don'tyou believe it, Rose. Don't!
- He couldn't have.

499
00:45:08,501 --> 00:45:11,163
Ofcourse he could.
It's easy enough for a professional.

500
00:45:11,237 --> 00:45:13,933
But I was with him the whole time.
This is absurd.

501
00:45:14,006 --> 00:45:18,636
Perhaps he did it whileyou were putting
your clothes back on, dear.

502
00:45:18,711 --> 00:45:20,941
Real slick, Cal.
Rose, they put it in my pocket.

503
00:45:21,013 --> 00:45:24,107
- Shut up.
- It isn't even your pocket, is it, son?

504
00:45:24,183 --> 00:45:27,243
Property ofA. L. Ryerson.

505
00:45:30,055 --> 00:45:32,455
- That was reported stolen today.
- I just borrowed it.

506
00:45:32,525 --> 00:45:36,188
- I was going to return it.
- We have an honest thief here, do we?

507
00:45:36,262 --> 00:45:39,493
You know I didn't do this, Rose.
You know it.

508
00:45:39,565 --> 00:45:42,500
Don'tyou believe them, Rose.
You know I didn't do it.

509
00:45:42,568 --> 00:45:44,798
- Come on, let's go.
- You know I didn't do it, Rose. Rose!

510
00:45:44,870 --> 00:45:47,304
Come on, son.
There's a good lad.

511
00:45:47,373 --> 00:45:50,809
- Come on.
- You know I didn't do it! You know me!

512
00:45:52,812 --> 00:45:55,440
Ismay:
Most unfortunate, Captain.

513
00:45:58,384 --> 00:46:01,876
Water... 1 4 feet above
the keel in ten minutes--

514
00:46:01,954 --> 00:46:05,446
In the forepeak, in all three holds
and in the boiler room six.

515
00:46:05,524 --> 00:46:08,220
- That's right, sir.
- When can we get underway, damn it?

516
00:46:08,294 --> 00:46:10,319
That's five compartments.

517
00:46:11,730 --> 00:46:15,427
She can stay afloat with the first
four compartments breached

518
00:46:15,501 --> 00:46:18,061
but not five-- not five.

519
00:46:18,137 --> 00:46:20,799
As she goes down bythe head
the water

520
00:46:20,873 --> 00:46:25,173
will spill overthe tops of bulkheads
at E deckfrom one to the next.

521
00:46:25,244 --> 00:46:28,145
Back and back.
There's no stopping it.

522
00:46:28,214 --> 00:46:30,148
The pumps--
Ifwe opened the doors--

523
00:46:30,216 --> 00:46:33,117
The pumps buyyou time,
but minutes only.

524
00:46:33,185 --> 00:46:36,018
From this moment,
no matterwhat we do

525
00:46:36,088 --> 00:46:39,080
Titanicwill founder.

526
00:46:41,227 --> 00:46:43,195
But this ship can't sink.

527
00:46:43,262 --> 00:46:46,288
She's made of iron, sir.
I assureyou, she can...

528
00:46:46,365 --> 00:46:48,765
and she will.

529
00:46:48,834 --> 00:46:51,359
It is a mathematical certainty.

530
00:46:54,640 --> 00:46:56,608
How much time?

531
00:47:03,516 --> 00:47:06,610
An hour. Two at most.

532
00:47:11,423 --> 00:47:14,392
And how many aboard,
Mr. Murdoch?

533
00:47:14,460 --> 00:47:17,452
2,200 souls on board, sir.

534
00:47:24,169 --> 00:47:28,572
Well, I believeyou may get
your headlines, Mr. Ismay.

535
00:47:45,404 --> 00:47:49,738
Oh, it is a little slut, isn't it? Will
you look at me when I'm talking toyou.

536
00:47:49,808 --> 00:47:51,742
( KnockAtDoor)

537
00:47:51,810 --> 00:47:53,744
- Mr. Hockley?
- Not now, we're busy.

538
00:47:53,812 --> 00:47:57,077
Sir, I've been told to askyou to please
put on your lifebelts and come up to--

539
00:47:57,149 --> 00:47:59,117
I said not now.

540
00:47:59,184 --> 00:48:02,244
I'm sorryto inconvenienceyou,
Mr. Hockley, but it's Captain's orders.

541
00:48:02,321 --> 00:48:05,848
Now, please, dress warmly.
It's quite cold out tonight.

542
00:48:05,924 --> 00:48:09,155
Now, may I suggest
topcoats and hats.

543
00:48:09,228 --> 00:48:13,392
- This is ridiculous.
- Not to worry, miss.

544
00:48:13,465 --> 00:48:15,490
I am sure
it'sjust a precaution.

545
00:48:15,567 --> 00:48:17,797
Everybody up!
Lifebelts on!

546
00:48:17,870 --> 00:48:20,930
- ( MenScreaming Orders)
- What's heyelling about?

547
00:48:21,006 --> 00:48:22,940
Everybody up!
Putyour lifebelts on!

548
00:48:23,008 --> 00:48:25,272
- What's the ruckus?
-Just putyour lifebelts on!

549
00:48:25,344 --> 00:48:27,744
Crewman:
C.QD.?

550
00:48:27,813 --> 00:48:29,747
Sir?

551
00:48:31,350 --> 00:48:33,784
That's right-- C.QD.
The distress call.

552
00:48:33,852 --> 00:48:35,786
That's our position.

553
00:48:38,156 --> 00:48:40,090
( Sighs)

554
00:48:40,158 --> 00:48:43,150
Tell whoever responds
that we're going down bythe head.

555
00:48:43,228 --> 00:48:46,197
We need immediate assistance.

556
00:48:54,373 --> 00:48:56,739
Blimey.

557
00:49:05,817 --> 00:49:10,186
Keep lowering!
Keep lowering!

558
00:49:15,127 --> 00:49:18,119
( Crewman Yelling OutOrders)

559
00:49:29,608 --> 00:49:32,771
Mr. Wilde! Mr. Wilde,
where are the passengers?

560
00:49:32,844 --> 00:49:36,280
We moved them back inside.
It's too damn cold and noisyforthem.

561
00:49:36,348 --> 00:49:38,782
You there!
(Blows Whistle)

562
00:49:38,850 --> 00:49:41,045
Get down here and
help with these lines.

563
00:49:41,119 --> 00:49:45,055
( Orchestra Playing
"Alexander's RagtimeBand")

564
00:49:47,626 --> 00:49:50,151
( People Conversing)

565
00:49:55,200 --> 00:49:57,293
Care for a drink, sir?

566
00:49:58,971 --> 00:50:01,769
- Crewman: Please putyour lifebelts on.
- Hey, sonny, what's doing?

567
00:50:01,840 --> 00:50:04,809
You got us all trussed up here
and now we're cooling our heels.

568
00:50:04,876 --> 00:50:06,969
Sorry, ma'am.
Let me go and find out.

569
00:50:07,045 --> 00:50:10,879
I don't think anybody knows
what the hell's going on around here.

570
00:50:10,949 --> 00:50:14,043
It's the goddamned English
doing everything bythe book.

571
00:50:14,119 --> 00:50:16,519
There's no need for language,
Mr. Hockley.

572
00:50:16,588 --> 00:50:18,818
Go back and turn
the heaters on in our rooms.

573
00:50:18,890 --> 00:50:20,858
I'd like a cup oftea
when I return.

574
00:50:20,926 --> 00:50:22,894
Yes, ma'am.

575
00:50:31,970 --> 00:50:34,063
Mr. Andrews.

576
00:50:35,173 --> 00:50:39,075
I saw the iceberg
and I see it in your eyes.

577
00:50:39,144 --> 00:50:41,635
Please tell me the truth.

578
00:50:48,887 --> 00:50:52,084
The ship will sink.

579
00:50:52,157 --> 00:50:56,150
- You're certain.
- Yes, in an hour or so....

580
00:50:56,228 --> 00:50:59,857
all this will be
at the bottom ofthe Atlantic.

581
00:50:59,931 --> 00:51:03,833
- What?
- Please, tell onlywhoyou must?

582
00:51:03,902 --> 00:51:06,393
I don't want to
be responsible for a panic

583
00:51:06,471 --> 00:51:09,463
and get to a boat quickly,
don't wait.

584
00:51:09,541 --> 00:51:12,374
You rememberwhat I told you
about the boats?

585
00:51:15,514 --> 00:51:17,448
Yes.

586
00:51:18,650 --> 00:51:21,210
I understand.

587
00:51:28,193 --> 00:51:30,593
Over here, sir.

588
00:51:30,662 --> 00:51:33,256
Sir, they need you
up in the second-class purser's office.

589
00:51:33,331 --> 00:51:35,891
- There's a big mob up there.
- Go on, I'll keep an eye on him.

590
00:51:35,967 --> 00:51:38,834
Aye, right.

591
00:51:51,950 --> 00:51:55,750
Sir! Carpathia says
they're making 1 7 knots.

592
00:51:55,821 --> 00:51:58,984
Full steam forthem, sir.

593
00:51:59,057 --> 00:52:00,991
She's the only one responding?

594
00:52:01,059 --> 00:52:04,358
The only one close, sir.
She says they can be here in four hours.

595
00:52:04,429 --> 00:52:06,795
Four hours?

596
00:52:11,570 --> 00:52:13,504
Thankyou, Bride.

597
00:52:17,375 --> 00:52:19,343
( Softly):
My God.

598
00:52:19,411 --> 00:52:23,006
( Crewmen Yelling OutOrders)

599
00:52:27,519 --> 00:52:30,920
Sir! We are swung out
and ready, sir.

600
00:52:32,057 --> 00:52:36,619
Hadn't we better get the women
and children into the boat, sir?

601
00:52:37,863 --> 00:52:40,730
- Yes, we do.
- Sir?

602
00:52:43,301 --> 00:52:47,533
Women and children first. Yes.

603
00:52:47,606 --> 00:52:49,540
Yes, sir.

604
00:52:51,376 --> 00:52:54,971
Crewman ( Yelling): Ladies
and gentlemen,your attention please!

605
00:52:55,046 --> 00:52:57,810
Step this way, please.
That's right.

606
00:52:57,883 --> 00:53:00,044
Come towards me.

607
00:53:00,118 --> 00:53:03,053
Thankyou. Good.

608
00:53:03,121 --> 00:53:07,581
Forthe time being, I shall require
onlywomen and children.

609
00:53:07,659 --> 00:53:09,991
Man:
Right here.

610
00:53:10,061 --> 00:53:12,029
All right, boys,
like the captain said

611
00:53:12,097 --> 00:53:14,429
nice and cheery
so there's no panic.

612
00:53:14,499 --> 00:53:16,433
"Wedding Dance."

613
00:53:16,501 --> 00:53:18,799
( Orchestra BeginsPlaying)

614
00:53:24,342 --> 00:53:27,311
Lifebelts on!
Here, putyour lifebelts on.

615
00:53:27,379 --> 00:53:30,746
Putyour lifebelts on.
Here, putyour lifebelt on.

616
00:53:30,815 --> 00:53:33,306
Here, come on, here.

617
00:53:35,287 --> 00:53:38,256
( Commotion)

618
00:53:38,323 --> 00:53:41,224
Crewman: It isn't time
to go up to the boatsyet.

619
00:53:41,293 --> 00:53:43,284
Please stay calm.

620
00:53:43,361 --> 00:53:46,387
Look, please, make sure, everybody,
you've gotyour lifebelts on

621
00:53:46,464 --> 00:53:49,490
and gentlemen, allow the women
and children through to the front.

622
00:53:49,568 --> 00:53:52,935
- What are we doing, Mommy?
- We'rejust waiting, dear.

623
00:53:53,004 --> 00:53:55,404
When they're finished putting
the first-class people in the boats...

624
00:53:55,473 --> 00:53:58,670
they'll start with us and
we'll want to be all ready, won't we?

625
00:53:58,743 --> 00:54:00,938
( MenArguing)

626
00:54:01,012 --> 00:54:03,105
Go and get some help.

627
00:54:03,181 --> 00:54:06,412
Lower away!
Left and right together!

628
00:54:06,484 --> 00:54:10,079
Steady! Both sides together.

629
00:54:10,155 --> 00:54:12,623
Steady! Steady!

630
00:54:12,691 --> 00:54:14,818
Steady!

631
00:54:14,893 --> 00:54:16,986
Stop! Stop!

632
00:54:17,062 --> 00:54:21,260
- ( Screaming)
- Hold the left side! Right side only!

633
00:54:21,333 --> 00:54:24,166
Right side only!
Right side only!

634
00:54:24,236 --> 00:54:26,761
Hold the left side!
Right side down!

635
00:54:26,838 --> 00:54:29,102
Lower awaytogether!

636
00:54:30,175 --> 00:54:32,109
Steady, lads!

637
00:54:35,413 --> 00:54:37,438
( Explosion)

638
00:54:37,515 --> 00:54:40,575
( Passengers Gasp )

639
00:55:19,324 --> 00:55:23,556
You know, I do believe
this ship may sink.

640
00:55:23,628 --> 00:55:26,563
I've been asked to giveyou

641
00:55:26,631 --> 00:55:29,532
this small token
ofour appreciation.

642
00:55:32,003 --> 00:55:34,870
Compliments of
Mr. Caledon Hockley.

643
00:55:41,012 --> 00:55:44,448
Come on, sister,you heard
the man-- into the boat.

644
00:55:44,516 --> 00:55:46,643
Any room for a gentleman,
gentlemen?

645
00:55:46,718 --> 00:55:49,949
Crewman:
Onlywomen at this time, sir.

646
00:55:50,021 --> 00:55:54,287
Will the lifeboats be seated
according to class?

647
00:55:55,727 --> 00:55:58,628
I hope they're
not too crowded.

648
00:55:58,697 --> 00:56:01,165
Oh, Mother, shut up!

649
00:56:01,232 --> 00:56:05,566
Don'tyou understand? The water is
freezing and there aren't enough boats.

650
00:56:05,637 --> 00:56:10,700
Not enough by half. Halfthe people
on this ship are going to die.

651
00:56:10,775 --> 00:56:12,709
Not the better half.

652
00:56:14,512 --> 00:56:18,505
Come on, Ruth, get in the boat.
First-class seats are right up here.

653
00:56:18,583 --> 00:56:20,915
You know, it's a pity
I didn't keep that drawing.

654
00:56:20,985 --> 00:56:23,920
It'll be worth
a lot more by morning.

655
00:56:26,458 --> 00:56:29,985
You unimaginable bastard.

656
00:56:30,061 --> 00:56:34,498
Molly: Come on, Rose, darling.
There's plenty of room foryou.

657
00:56:34,566 --> 00:56:36,761
Come on, Rose.
You're next, darling.

658
00:56:36,835 --> 00:56:38,769
Come into the boat, Rose.

659
00:56:41,272 --> 00:56:46,073
- Come.
- Rose, get into the boat.

660
00:56:46,144 --> 00:56:48,510
Rose.

661
00:56:48,580 --> 00:56:50,548
Good-bye, Mother.

662
00:56:52,384 --> 00:56:55,148
Rose! Rose, come back here!

663
00:56:55,220 --> 00:56:58,348
Where areyou going?
To him?

664
00:56:58,423 --> 00:57:01,187
To be a whore to a gutter rat?

665
00:57:01,259 --> 00:57:03,955
I'd rather be his whore
than yourwife.

666
00:57:06,731 --> 00:57:08,961
No. No!

667
00:57:09,033 --> 00:57:12,127
- I said no!
- ( Hawking)

668
00:57:12,203 --> 00:57:14,228
Ruth:
Rose! Please stop!

669
00:57:14,305 --> 00:57:16,364
Crewman:
And lower away!

670
00:57:16,441 --> 00:57:18,409
- Rose!
- Man the tiller!

671
00:57:18,476 --> 00:57:20,740
- No, wait!
- Lower away!

672
00:57:20,812 --> 00:57:23,178
- Rose!
- Lowertogether!

673
00:57:28,219 --> 00:57:30,517
Help!

674
00:57:30,588 --> 00:57:32,749
Can anybody hear me?

675
00:57:32,824 --> 00:57:35,816
( BangingPipe)
Hello, help me!

676
00:57:35,894 --> 00:57:39,091
( Distantly):
Help me!

677
00:57:39,164 --> 00:57:41,758
Can anybody hear me?

678
00:57:41,833 --> 00:57:45,860
Somebody help me, please!

679
00:57:45,937 --> 00:57:48,167
Rose:
Mr. Andrews?

680
00:57:50,642 --> 00:57:53,543
- Steward, checkthe starboard corridor.
- Yes, Mr. Andrews.

681
00:57:53,611 --> 00:57:56,136
Madam, please put on a lifebelt.
Get to the boat deck immediately.

682
00:57:56,214 --> 00:57:58,409
Lucy, for God's sake,
put on your lifebelt.

683
00:57:58,483 --> 00:58:00,644
- Set a good example.
- Yes, sir.

684
00:58:00,718 --> 00:58:04,154
- Anyone in here?
- Mr. Andrews? Mr. Andrews, thank God.

685
00:58:04,222 --> 00:58:06,486
Where would the master-at-arms
take someone under arrest?

686
00:58:06,558 --> 00:58:09,288
What? You have to get
to a boat right away.

687
00:58:09,360 --> 00:58:13,797
No! I'm doing this with orwithoutyour
help, sir, but without will take longer.

688
00:58:16,468 --> 00:58:20,302
Take the elevatorto the bottom. Go
to the left down the crewman's passage.

689
00:58:20,371 --> 00:58:24,637
Then go right and left again at the
stairs. You'll come to a long corridor.

690
00:58:29,514 --> 00:58:32,039
- This could be bad.
- (WaterGurgling)

691
00:58:34,752 --> 00:58:38,085
Oh, shit. Oh, shit!

692
00:58:39,324 --> 00:58:42,725
( Struggling)

693
00:58:42,794 --> 00:58:46,025
- Excuse me, thankyou.
- Crewman: The lifts are closed.

694
00:58:46,097 --> 00:58:48,827
- Woman: I do not care...
- The lifts are--

695
00:58:48,900 --> 00:58:52,336
I'm sorry, miss,
but the lifts are closed.

696
00:58:52,403 --> 00:58:57,170
I'm through being polite, goddamn it!
Now take me down!

697
00:58:57,242 --> 00:58:59,176
E deck.

698
00:59:02,947 --> 00:59:05,472
Come on. Oh, come on.

699
00:59:07,986 --> 00:59:09,954
( Yells)

700
00:59:20,765 --> 00:59:22,858
( Screams)

701
00:59:22,934 --> 00:59:25,630
- I'm going back up!
- No!

702
00:59:25,703 --> 00:59:27,933
No, no!

703
00:59:30,975 --> 00:59:32,966
Come back!
I'm going back up.

704
00:59:33,044 --> 00:59:35,342
I'm going back up!

705
00:59:43,154 --> 00:59:45,850
Crew passage.

706
00:59:45,924 --> 00:59:48,051
Crew passage.

707
00:59:57,769 --> 01:00:01,205
( BreathingHard)

708
01:00:07,712 --> 01:00:09,236
Jack?

709
01:00:12,617 --> 01:00:14,346
Jack?

710
01:00:18,189 --> 01:00:20,487
Jack?!

711
01:00:20,558 --> 01:00:22,526
-Jack?
- Rose!

712
01:00:22,594 --> 01:00:24,789
Jack?!

713
01:00:24,862 --> 01:00:27,422
Rose, I'm in here!
I'm in here.

714
01:00:27,498 --> 01:00:29,966
-Jack?!
- I'm in here.

715
01:00:30,034 --> 01:00:31,968
-Jack?!
- Rose!

716
01:00:32,036 --> 01:00:34,266
Jack!Jack! I'm sorry.

717
01:00:34,339 --> 01:00:36,705
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

718
01:00:37,775 --> 01:00:41,472
- That guy Lovejoy put it in my pocket.
- I know, I know, I know, I know.

719
01:00:41,546 --> 01:00:44,811
Listen, Rose,you're going to have
to find a spare key, all right?

720
01:00:44,882 --> 01:00:47,578
Look in that cabinet
right there.

721
01:00:47,652 --> 01:00:50,212
It's a little
silver one, Rose.

722
01:00:50,288 --> 01:00:52,222
Silver.

723
01:00:52,290 --> 01:00:56,226
- These are all brass ones!
- Check right here, Rose.

724
01:01:00,264 --> 01:01:02,289
Rose...

725
01:01:02,367 --> 01:01:04,528
how did you find out
I didn't do it?

726
01:01:04,602 --> 01:01:06,570
I didn't.

727
01:01:06,638 --> 01:01:09,630
I just realized I already knew.

728
01:01:10,675 --> 01:01:13,303
- Keep looking.
- Oh.

729
01:01:20,118 --> 01:01:23,554
No key. There's no key!

730
01:01:23,621 --> 01:01:27,182
All right, Rose, listen. You're going
to have to go find some help.

731
01:01:27,258 --> 01:01:29,385
It'll be all right.

732
01:01:33,765 --> 01:01:35,699
I'll be right back.

733
01:01:42,940 --> 01:01:45,500
I'lljust wait here.

734
01:01:57,255 --> 01:01:59,416
Hello, is there anyone here?

735
01:02:00,591 --> 01:02:04,049
Hello? ls there anybody
down here?

736
01:02:05,363 --> 01:02:07,354
We need help! Hello!

737
01:02:07,432 --> 01:02:09,195
Damn it.

738
01:02:15,440 --> 01:02:19,843
Can anybody hear me?
Please, hello! Hello!

739
01:02:21,312 --> 01:02:24,679
Oh, thank God.
Wait, please, I need your help.

740
01:02:24,749 --> 01:02:27,217
There's a man back here and--
Wait!

741
01:02:31,589 --> 01:02:33,921
Hello?

742
01:02:44,335 --> 01:02:47,566
( LoudRumbling)

743
01:02:47,638 --> 01:02:50,903
( RoseBreathingHard)

744
01:02:58,850 --> 01:03:02,081
- Hello?
- Ah, miss,you shouldn't be here now.

745
01:03:02,153 --> 01:03:04,781
- Please, I need your help.
- This way, quickly.

746
01:03:04,856 --> 01:03:07,916
There is a man down here
and he is trapped. Please.

747
01:03:07,992 --> 01:03:10,085
- There's no need to panic.
- No, I'm not panicking.

748
01:03:10,161 --> 01:03:12,391
You're going the wrong way!

749
01:03:12,463 --> 01:03:14,727
Let go of me, listen!

750
01:03:19,437 --> 01:03:23,168
- To hell with you.
- Oh!

751
01:03:23,241 --> 01:03:25,732
( Ship Creaking)

752
01:03:58,543 --> 01:04:00,534
( Softly):
Oh, my God...

753
01:04:05,216 --> 01:04:07,878
- ( Explosion)
- ( Crackling)

754
01:04:18,963 --> 01:04:21,193
( Gasping)

755
01:04:39,050 --> 01:04:42,508
( LoudRumbling)

756
01:04:48,693 --> 01:04:52,094
-Jack!
- Rose!

757
01:04:52,163 --> 01:04:56,259
- Will this work?
- I guess we'll find out.

758
01:04:56,334 --> 01:04:58,325
Come on.

759
01:05:00,338 --> 01:05:04,274
Wait, wait, wait, wait. Try a couple
of practice swings overthere.

760
01:05:04,342 --> 01:05:06,936
All right.

761
01:05:09,513 --> 01:05:13,244
Good, now tryto hit
the same mark again, Rose.

762
01:05:13,317 --> 01:05:15,285
You can do it.

763
01:05:19,991 --> 01:05:22,391
Okay, that's enough practice.

764
01:05:22,460 --> 01:05:25,452
Come on, Rose,
you can do it. Listen.

765
01:05:25,529 --> 01:05:28,396
Just hit it really hard
and reallyfast.

766
01:05:29,834 --> 01:05:33,099
Wait, open your hands up
a little more.

767
01:05:33,170 --> 01:05:35,331
- Like that?
- Right.

768
01:05:35,406 --> 01:05:38,170
Listen, Rose, I trustyou.

769
01:05:42,546 --> 01:05:44,480
Go!

770
01:05:44,548 --> 01:05:47,016
-( Clang)
-( Gasps)

771
01:05:47,084 --> 01:05:49,746
( ScreamingAndLaughing)

772
01:05:49,820 --> 01:05:53,153
You did it!
Come on, let's go.

773
01:05:53,224 --> 01:05:55,920
Oh, shit, this is cold.
Oh, shit!

774
01:05:55,993 --> 01:05:57,722
Shit, shit.

775
01:06:04,368 --> 01:06:08,304
- This is the way out.
- We have to find anotherway. Come on.

776
01:06:08,372 --> 01:06:11,205
- Tiller: Pull.
- (Orchestra Playing)

777
01:06:11,275 --> 01:06:15,211
Pull!
Putyour backs into it, pull!

778
01:06:15,279 --> 01:06:19,113
( DistantShouting)

779
01:06:19,183 --> 01:06:21,117
Pull!

780
01:06:21,185 --> 01:06:24,120
Now, there's something
you don't see every day.

781
01:06:24,188 --> 01:06:26,622
Pull!

782
01:06:30,061 --> 01:06:32,427
( DistantExplosion)

783
01:06:34,298 --> 01:06:37,131
( Shouting)

784
01:06:46,444 --> 01:06:48,776
Crewman:
What's this luggage doing here?

785
01:06:48,846 --> 01:06:53,783
- Get rid of it, we need the room.
- (Crewman Giving Orders)

786
01:06:53,851 --> 01:06:55,819
( Crying)

787
01:06:55,886 --> 01:06:57,820
Keep calm.

788
01:06:57,888 --> 01:07:00,015
No!

789
01:07:04,295 --> 01:07:07,594
-Lovejoy.
-She's not on the starboard side either.

790
01:07:07,665 --> 01:07:10,225
We're running out oftime
and this strutting martinet

791
01:07:10,301 --> 01:07:12,235
isn't letting
any men on at all.

792
01:07:12,303 --> 01:07:14,897
There's one on the other side
letting men on.

793
01:07:14,972 --> 01:07:19,671
Well, then, that's our play. We'll need
some insurance first. Come on.

794
01:07:19,744 --> 01:07:21,769
- ( Pounding)
- This way.

795
01:07:21,846 --> 01:07:25,441
- All the way down here.
- (Jack Yelling)

796
01:07:25,516 --> 01:07:29,816
Steward:
Here! What doyou thinkyou're doing?

797
01:07:29,887 --> 01:07:33,288
You'll have to payforthat,you know.
That's White Star Line property.

798
01:07:33,357 --> 01:07:36,224
Both:
Shut up!

799
01:07:36,293 --> 01:07:40,491
Will you hold the boat a moment?
I just have to run backto my room--

800
01:07:40,564 --> 01:07:44,125
Sit down! She's the last.
All right to lower.

801
01:07:44,201 --> 01:07:47,295
Mr. Lightoller, why are the boats
being launched halffull?

802
01:07:47,371 --> 01:07:50,465
- Not now, Mr. Andrews.
- There, look, 20 or so

803
01:07:50,541 --> 01:07:54,238
in a boat built for 65,
and I saw one boat with only 1 2-- 1 2!

804
01:07:54,311 --> 01:07:58,645
Well, we weren't sure ofthe weight,
Mr. Andrews. These boats may buckle.

805
01:07:58,716 --> 01:08:03,119
Rubbish! Theywere tested in Belfast
with the weight of70 men!

806
01:08:03,187 --> 01:08:06,714
Now, fill these boats,
Mr. Lightoller, for God's sake, man!

807
01:08:12,763 --> 01:08:15,994
Please, I need more women
and children, please.

808
01:08:20,004 --> 01:08:22,996
Crewman: Get back in there.
This is not an exit.

809
01:08:23,074 --> 01:08:25,702
Get back in there.
This is not an exit.

810
01:08:27,812 --> 01:08:31,543
You can't keep us locked in here like
animals. The ship's bloody sinking!

